  "text": "In particular, letting N = F be free, a homomorphism M → F , such that the induced morphism G M → G F is injective, is a versal map in the terminology of [CITATION_1] . Given such a map, the theorem implies that R(M ) → R(F ) = Sym(F ) is injective, recovering another result of [CITATION_2] , namely that the Rees algebra of M can be computed as R(M ) = im Sym(M ) → Sym(F ) .",
