      "span_text": "Given such a map, the theorem implies that R(M ) → R(F ) = Sym(F ) is injective, recovering another result of [CITATION_2] , namely that the Rees algebra of M can be computed as R(M ) = im Sym(M ) → Sym(F ) ."
